{"title_page": "After We Collided", "text_new": "{{short description|Film directed by Roger Kumble}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = After We Collided\n| image          = \n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Roger Kumble]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Anna Todd]]\n* [[Jennifer Gibgot]]\n* [[Mark Canton]]\n* [[Courtney Solomon]]\n* [[Adam Shankman]]\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Anna Todd]]\n* Mario Celaya\n}}\n| based on       = {{Based on|''After We Collided''|[[Anna Todd]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Josephine Langford]]\n* [[Hero Fiennes-Tiffin]]\n* [[Louise Lombard]]\n* [[Dylan Sprouse]]\n* [[Candice King]]\n* [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]]\n}}\n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[Justin Burnett]]\n| cinematography = Larry Reibman\n| editing        = Anita Brandt-Burgoyne\n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* CalMaple Media\n* [[Offspring Entertainment]]\n* [[Voltage Pictures]]\n}}\n| distributor    = \n| released       = \n| runtime        = \n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n'''''After We Collided''''' is an upcoming [[romantic drama]] film starring [[Josephine Langford]] and [[Hero Fiennes-Tiffin]] and directed by [[Roger Kumble]]. It is based on the 2014 [[new adult fiction]] novel of the same name written by Anna Todd and is the sequel to the film ''[[After (2019 film)|After]]''. The story follows Tessa Young, a college student and her relationship with a \u2018bad boy\u2019 Hardin Scott, after the big reveal - Bet.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Josephine Langford]] as Tessa Young\n* [[Hero Fiennes-Tiffin]] as Hardin Scott\n** John Jackson Hunter as young Hardin\n* [[Louise Lombard]] as Trish Daniels\n* [[Dylan Sprouse]] as Trevor Matthews\n* [[Candice King]] as Kimberly\n* [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]] as Christian Vance\n* Max Ragone as Smith Vance\n* [[Selma Blair]] as Carol Young\n* [[Shane Paul McGhie]] as Landon Gibson\n* [[Rob Estes]] as Ken Scott\n* [[Karimah Westbrook]] as Karen Scott\n* Khadijha Red Thunder as Steph Jones\n* [[Inanna Sarkis]] as Molly Samuels\n* [[Samuel Larsen]] as Zed Evans\n* [[Pia Mia]] as Tristan\n* [[Dylan Arnold]] as Noah Porter\n\n==Production==\nIn May 2019, it was confirmed that a sequel to the film ''[[After (2019 film)|After]]'' was planned with [[Josephine Langford]] and [[Hero Fiennes Tiffin]] reprising their roles as Tessa Young and Hardin Scott respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/after-sequel-josephine-langford-hero-fiennes-tiffin-anna-todd-voltage-cannes-1202618418/|title=Voltage Heats Up 'After' Sequel; Josephine Langford & Hero Fiennes Tiffin Returning \u2013 Cannes|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|date=May 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn August 4, it was announced that [[Roger Kumble]] would direct the sequel.<ref name=\"deadline\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/dylan-sprouse-after-we-collided-roger-kumble-directing-after-sequel-1202663658/|title='Cruel Intentions' Director Roger Kumble Takes On After Sequel After We Collided Starring Dylan Sprouse|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|date=7 August 2019|website=Deadline|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> On August 5, it was announced that [[Dylan Sprouse]] was cast as Trevor, Tessa's coworker.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/dylan-sprouse-after-sequel-fucking-trevor|title=Dylan Sprouse Will Play 'F-cking Trevor' In The After Sequel|last=Logan|first=Elizabeth|date=August 5, 2019|accessdate=August 5, 2019|publisher=W Magazine}}</ref> On August 15, [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]], [[Rob Estes]], [[Louise Lombard]], [[Candice King]], [[Karimah Westbrook]] and Max Ragone were announced to play Christian Vance, Ken Scott, Trish, Kim, Karen, and Smith, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/after-we-collided-cast-candice-king-charlie-weber-louise-lombard-anna-todd-after-sequel-1202668712/|title='After We Collided' Rounds Out Cast With Charlie Weber, Louise Lombard, Candice King & More|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|date=August 15, 2019|accessdate=August 16, 2019|work=Deadline}}</ref> Estes and Westbrook replaced [[Peter Gallagher]] and [[Jennifer Beals]] as Ken and Karen Scott respectively.\n\n===Filming===\n[[Principal photography]] began in August 2019 in [[Atlanta, Georgia]].<ref>{{cite tweet|user=aftermovie|number=1160907215500468224|date=August 12, 2019|title=We can confirm that cameras are now rolling and the first scenes for #AfterWeCollidedMovie are now being shot.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com.au/culture/features/dylan-sprouse-has-been-cast-in-the-sequel-to-after/news-story/ae76009aee4da791200376b9b4d2e170|title=Dylan Sprouse has been cast in the sequel of After|last=Xidias|first=Angelica|date=August 6, 2019|accessdate=August 16, 2019|publisher=Vogue Australia}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|10362466}}\n* ''[https://www.wattpad.com/story/5095707-after After]'', the novel which serves as the basis for the movie, on [[Wattpad]]\n\n{{Roger Kumble}}\n\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:Films based on American novels]]\n[[Category:Films based on romance novels]]\n[[Category:Films based on young adult literature]]\n[[Category:Films set in universities and colleges]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Atlanta]]\n[[Category:One Direction]]\n[[Category:Fan fiction works]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Roger Kumble]]\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Film directed by Roger Kumble}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = After We Collided\n| image          = \n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Roger Kumble]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Anna Todd]]\n* [[Jennifer Gibgot]]\n* [[Mark Canton]]\n* [[Courtney Solomon]]\n* [[Adam Shankman]]\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Anna Todd]]\n* Mario Celaya\n}}\n| based on       = {{Based on|''After We Collided''|[[Anna Todd]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Josephine Langford]]\n* [[Hero Fiennes-Tiffin]]\n* [[Louise Lombard]]\n* [[Dylan Sprouse]]\n* [[Candice King]]\n* [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]]\n}}\n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[Justin Burnett]]\n| cinematography = Larry Reibman\n| editing        = Anita Brandt-Burgoyne\n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* CalMaple Media\n* [[Offspring Entertainment]]\n* [[Voltage Pictures]]\n}}\n| distributor    = TBA\n| released       = 2020\n| runtime        = \n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n'''''After We Collided''''' is an upcoming [[romantic drama]] film starring [[Josephine Langford]] and [[Hero Fiennes-Tiffin]] and directed by [[Roger Kumble]]. It is based on the 2014 [[new adult fiction]] novel of the same name written by Anna Todd and is the sequel to the film ''[[After (2019 film)|After]]''. The story follows Tessa Young, a college student and her relationship with a \u2018bad boy\u2019 Hardin Scott, after the big reveal - Bet.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Josephine Langford]] as Tessa Young\n* [[Hero Fiennes-Tiffin]] as Hardin Scott\n** John Jackson Hunter as young Hardin\n* [[Louise Lombard]] as Trish Daniels\n* [[Dylan Sprouse]] as Trevor Matthews\n* [[Candice King]] as Kimberly\n* [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]] as Christian Vance\n* Max Ragone as Smith Vance\n* [[Selma Blair]] as Carol Young\n* [[Shane Paul McGhie]] as Landon Gibson\n* [[Rob Estes]] as Ken Scott\n* [[Karimah Westbrook]] as Karen Scott\n* Khadijha Red Thunder as Steph Jones\n* [[Inanna Sarkis]] as Molly Samuels\n* [[Samuel Larsen]] as Zed Evans\n* [[Pia Mia]] as Tristan\n* [[Dylan Arnold]] as Noah Porter\n\n==Production==\nIn May 2019, it was confirmed that a sequel to the film ''[[After (2019 film)|After]]'' was planned with [[Josephine Langford]] and [[Hero Fiennes Tiffin]] reprising their roles as Tessa Young and Hardin Scott respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/after-sequel-josephine-langford-hero-fiennes-tiffin-anna-todd-voltage-cannes-1202618418/|title=Voltage Heats Up 'After' Sequel; Josephine Langford & Hero Fiennes Tiffin Returning \u2013 Cannes|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|date=May 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn August 4, it was announced that [[Roger Kumble]] would direct the sequel.<ref name=\"deadline\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/dylan-sprouse-after-we-collided-roger-kumble-directing-after-sequel-1202663658/|title='Cruel Intentions' Director Roger Kumble Takes On After Sequel After We Collided Starring Dylan Sprouse|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|date=7 August 2019|website=Deadline|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> On August 5, it was announced that [[Dylan Sprouse]] was cast as Trevor, Tessa's coworker.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/dylan-sprouse-after-sequel-fucking-trevor|title=Dylan Sprouse Will Play 'F-cking Trevor' In The After Sequel|last=Logan|first=Elizabeth|date=August 5, 2019|accessdate=August 5, 2019|publisher=W Magazine}}</ref> On August 14, John Jackson Hunter was cast as young Hardin.{{cn|date=January 2020}} On August 15, [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]], [[Rob Estes]], [[Louise Lombard]], [[Candice King]], [[Karimah Westbrook]] and Max Ragone were announced to play Christian Vance, Ken Scott, Trish, Kim, Karen, and Smith, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/after-we-collided-cast-candice-king-charlie-weber-louise-lombard-anna-todd-after-sequel-1202668712/|title='After We Collided' Rounds Out Cast With Charlie Weber, Louise Lombard, Candice King & More|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|date=August 15, 2019|accessdate=August 16, 2019|work=Deadline}}</ref> Estes and Westbrook replaced [[Peter Gallagher]] and [[Jennifer Beals]] as Ken and Karen Scott respectively.\n\n===Filming===\n[[Principal photography]] began in August 2019 in [[Atlanta, Georgia]].<ref>{{cite tweet|user=aftermovie|number=1160907215500468224|date=August 12, 2019|title=We can confirm that cameras are now rolling and the first scenes for #AfterWeCollidedMovie are now being shot.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com.au/culture/features/dylan-sprouse-has-been-cast-in-the-sequel-to-after/news-story/ae76009aee4da791200376b9b4d2e170|title=Dylan Sprouse has been cast in the sequel of After|last=Xidias|first=Angelica|date=August 6, 2019|accessdate=August 16, 2019|publisher=Vogue Australia}}</ref> Filming concluded on September 16, 2019.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\nThe teaser trailer was released on February 14, 2020.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|10362466}}\n* ''[https://www.wattpad.com/story/5095707-after After]'', the novel which serves as the basis for the movie, on [[Wattpad]]\n\n{{Roger Kumble}}\n\n[[Category:2020s romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:Films based on American novels]]\n[[Category:Films based on romance novels]]\n[[Category:Films based on young adult literature]]\n[[Category:Films set in universities and colleges]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Atlanta]]\n[[Category:One Direction]]\n[[Category:Fan fiction works]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Roger Kumble]]\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n", "name_user": "Bovineboy2008", "label": "safe", "comment": "remove unsourced statements", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/After_We_Collided"}
